{"key":"post-12833332","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12833332</id>\n<content>Actually, cutting right at the base is fine.&amp;nbsp; A damaged spot on a substrate from ripping mushrooms out is as prone to contamination as the left over stem butt.&amp;nbsp; Remember, cakes are mycelium, and mushrooms are 100% mycelium.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To the original poster, the q-tip test is bunk.&amp;nbsp; Bruised mycelium will often rub off on the q-tip and this has resulted in way too many good cakes being tossed out.&amp;nbsp; Mold spores look like a separate layer of green sand on the surface, while bruising looks like a bruise on your knee.&amp;nbsp; It's the color of the skin itself, as in your pictures above.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12834856</next>\n<prev>12833252</prev>\n<first>12832761</first>\n<last>12838440</last>\n<when>1277990791</when>\n<utime>07/01/10 04:26 PM</utime>\n</post>"}